	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_CSBULLBLOOD">
			<Text>Bulls Blood Warrior</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_ANTIQUITY_CSBULLBLOOD_TEXT">
			<Text>
				"In time of war the men undergo a treatment supposed to communicate stregth and bravery to them. A bull is thrown to the groudn, its foreleg cut off... The meat, after being anointed with charms, is given to the warriors, who are also sprinkled with the blood of the bull" - H. E. Mabille, The Basuto of Basutoland (Oxford, 1906).
			</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_CSBULLBLOOD_STRATEGY">
			<Text>A Musketman replacement that ains a unique 'War Charm' promotion after entering combat for the first time. A 1 in 4 chance of either- A combat bonus adjacent to friendly units, a combat bonus fighting in hills, both of these bonuses, or nothing!
			</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_HELP_CSBULLBLOOD">
			<Text>Lesotho's Musketman replacement. Gains a random unique promotion the first time it enters combat.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
